# Cloudflare static-asset cache policy. Three classes by mutability:
#
#   _astro/*  — Astro fingerprints these (name changes on content change) → immutable.
#   data/*    — content-hashed by scripts/hash-data.mjs (name changes on content
#               change) → immutable. INVARIANT: nothing is fetched at runtime by an
#               UN-hashed /data/ URL; the short reads inline their JSON at build time.
#               If that ever changes, an un-hashed runtime fetch would serve stale
#               data under this rule — hash it (add to RUNTIME_FILES in hash-data.mjs).
#   og/, thumbs/ — regenerated each deploy, referenced by stable name → short TTL.
#   /*        — HTML: always revalidate so a new deploy's fresh URLs are picked up.
#
# IMPORTANT — Workers Static Assets COMBINES every matching rule's headers (there is
# NO most-specific-wins). A request to /data/x.json matches both /data/* and the /*
# catch-all, so without intervention its Cache-Control becomes the two values joined
# by a comma ("max-age=0, must-revalidate, max-age=31536000, immutable") — the
# max-age=0 wins and immutable is defeated. So every specific rule first UNSETS the
# inherited Cache-Control with `! Cache-Control`, then sets its own. Verified with
# `curl -I` post-deploy. Docs: developers.cloudflare.com/workers/static-assets/headers

/_astro/*
  ! Cache-Control
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/data/*
  ! Cache-Control
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

# Maps are fetched at runtime under a STABLE name (not hashed) — boundary geojson
# that essentially never changes. Not immutable (a correction must be able to
# propagate); a day's cache with background revalidation is the safe middle.
/maps/*
  ! Cache-Control
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400, stale-while-revalidate=604800

/og/*
  ! Cache-Control
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600, must-revalidate

/thumbs/*
  ! Cache-Control
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600, must-revalidate

# Security headers ride the catch-all so they apply everywhere (rules COMBINE,
# see note above — the specific cache rules only unset Cache-Control, so these
# survive on /data/* etc.). CSP notes:
#   - script-src needs 'unsafe-inline': Astro emits is:inline bootstrap scripts
#     (theme/units) into every page; a static site can't nonce them.
#   - buttondown.com: newsletter form POST (no-JS path) + fetch (enhanced path).
#   - cloudflareinsights.com: the optional Web Analytics beacon (script from
#     static.cloudflareinsights.com, data POSTed to cloudflareinsights.com).
#   - img-src data:: ECharts/inline SVG data URIs.
/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://static.cloudflareinsights.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self' https://cloudflareinsights.com https://buttondown.com; form-action 'self' https://buttondown.com; frame-ancestors 'self'; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none'
